    "Figure 14 presents how features are extracted at multiple scales, resulting in a feature pyramid that captures information at different levels of detail and abstraction.",
    "CentripetalNet demonstrates higher prediction accuracy than the bounding box approach in FPN.",
    "It achieves finegrained localization of potential objects within an image and delivers superior performance in challenging scenarios, such as dense or crowded scenes and partially visible objects.",
    "The architecture of CentripetalNet, illustrated in Figure 15, leverages key points for object detection.",
    "Kivee (Dong et al., 2020) developed CentripetalNet to pursue high-quality keypoint pairs for object detection, addressing issues related to inaccurate keypoint matching and limited feature integration, which often result in the loss of spatial context and essential information for effective object detection."
